1:# Architecture
2:
3:## Overview
4:
5:Civ-engine is a general-purpose, headless, AI-native 2D grid-based game engine. Built in Node.js/TypeScript with a strict ECS (Entity-Component-System) architecture.
6:
7:**AI-native** means the engine is designed to be operated by AI agents, not human players directly. Humans provide high-level game designs; AI agents write game logic, submit commands, and observe state. Every design decision prioritizes machine-readability: deterministic tick execution, JSON-serializable state, structured diffs, typed command/event interfaces, and a purely programmatic API with no interactive UI.
8:
9:The engine provides reusable infrastructure (entities, components, spatial indexing, events, commands, resources, serialization) that game projects consume. It outputs state changes that a separate client can render; it contains no game-specific logic, rendering, or UI code.
10:
11:## Component Map
12:
13:| Component      | File                     | Responsibility                                                                         |
14:| -------------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
15:| World          | `src/world.ts`           | Top-level API, owns all subsystems, phased system pipeline, metrics, spatial index sync |
16:| EntityManager  | `src/entity-manager.ts`  | Entity creation/destruction, ID recycling via free-list, generation counters           |
17:| ComponentStore | `src/component-store.ts` | Sparse array storage per component type, generation counter for change detection       |
18:| SpatialGrid    | `src/spatial-grid.ts`    | Sparse occupied-cell grid plus read-only view, neighbor/radius queries                 |
19:| GameLoop       | `src/game-loop.ts`       | Fixed-timestep loop, step() for testing, start()/stop() for real-time, speed multiplier, pause/resume |
20:| EventBus       | `src/event-bus.ts`       | Typed pub/sub event bus, per-tick buffer, listener registry                            |
21:| CommandQueue   | `src/command-queue.ts`   | Typed command buffer, push/drain interface                                             |
22:| Serializer     | `src/serializer.ts`      | Versioned WorldSnapshot types for state serialization                                  |
23:| Diff           | `src/diff.ts`            | TickDiff type for per-tick change sets                                                 |
24:| ResourceStore  | `src/resource-store.ts`  | Resource pools, production/consumption rates, transfers, dirty tracking                |
25:| OccupancyGrid  | `src/occupancy-grid.ts`  | Deterministic blocked-cell, footprint, reservation, lifecycle binding, blocker metadata, metrics, and sub-cell crowding tracking |
26:| JSON helpers   | `src/json.ts`            | JSON-compatible component validation and fingerprints for mutation detection           |
27:| Noise          | `src/noise.ts`           | Seedable 2D simplex noise, octave layering utility                                     |
28:| Cellular       | `src/cellular.ts`        | Cellular automata step function, immutable CellGrid                                    |
29:| MapGen         | `src/map-gen.ts`         | MapGenerator interface, createTileGrid bulk tile-entity helper                         |
30:| Pathfinding    | `src/pathfinding.ts`     | Generic A* pathfinding, graph-agnostic with user-defined callbacks          |
31:| Path Service   | `src/path-service.ts`    | Grid path helper, deterministic path queue, and cache for batched request handling     |
32:| RenderAdapter  | `src/render-adapter.ts`  | Projects world state into renderer-facing snapshots and diffs with generation-aware refs |
33:| ScenarioRunner | `src/scenario-runner.ts` | Headless setup/run/check harness built on World, WorldDebugger, and WorldHistoryRecorder |
34:| VisibilityMap  | `src/visibility-map.ts`  | Per-player visible/explored cell tracking for fog-of-war style mechanics               |
35:| WorldDebugger  | `src/world-debugger.ts`  | Structured debug snapshots, warnings, and probe helpers for engine and standalone utilities |
36:| ClientAdapter  | `src/client-adapter.ts`  | Bridges World API to typed client messages via send callback |
37:| BehaviorTree   | `src/behavior-tree.ts`   | Generic BT framework: NodeStatus, BTNode, Selector, Sequence, ReactiveSelector, ReactiveSequence, Action, Condition, BTState, createBehaviorTree, clearRunningState |
